a pawn back.} 6. Nc3 {White develops the pieces and makes pressure on the d5
pawn.} Nc6 {This is a mistake that will cost Black a pawn and makes his
position hard to play.} 7. exd5 exd5 8. Qh5+ {Here you can see how the
f6-weakness can be exploited. This variation is hard to play for Black because
he always has to think about the Qh5 move.} g6 9. Qxd5 {With an extra pawn and
a clear advantage for White.} *

