White good chances to get an overwhelming initiative for the b2-pawn.} 4. Nf3 {
White sacrifices a pawn for the initiative. The moves will be quite forced for
some time. Black will lose time taking the b2-pawn and then lose some more
time to getting the queen back. White will use these tempi to obtain a big
advantage in development. In my opinion, this line is tricky to play for Black,
and the 3... Bf5 variations look much more solid. White will get a very
easy-to-play position with a clear plan and a lot of pressure.} Qxb2 {Black
has to take the pawn. Otherwise, the queen move was pointless. The only real
alternative is to play 4...Bf5 , with a transposition to the 3. ..Bf5
variation.} 5. Nbd2 {A developing move that also defends the rook.} Nf6 {Black
is behind in development, so he has to start bringing out his pieces on the
kingside and castle. Please note that Black cannot develop the light square
bishop right now because of Rb1.} 6. Bd3 {The best square for the bishop. It
will support the e4-break after castling.} Qa3 {Black can try this setup as
well. Let us see what could happen here.} 7. O-O {White hides the king and has
the upper hand for the upcoming action.} h6 {Black plays ...h6 intending to
play ...g5 next and then fianchetto the dark-squared bishop.} 8. Bh4 g5 9. Bg3
Bg7 10. Rb1 {A nice positional move. White puts the rook on the open file to
put pressure on the b7-pawn, not allowing the Black light-squared bishop to
get into play.} Nbd7 {The bishop has to stay to defend the b7-pawn, so Black
develops the knight first.} 11. Qe2 {Again a smart positional move from White.
He improves the position of the queen, connects the rooks and prepares the e4
and c4 central breaks.} O-O 12. c4 {The position is great for White. Even
though Black is a pawn up, White has more than enough compensation. Black is
without any play, struggles with piece development, and has to be careful with
his queen. Again, in this variation, if Black takes the pawn on b2, White gets
a tremendous amount of pressure in exchange. In my opinion, the pawn is not
worth handing over such an initiative, and Black should avoid it.} *

